<br>
Considering even a single mithril is an enormous sum of money, if the typical d00d gamer could reproduce this, they could completely destroy the money economy of any server.  Also imagine the poor fool who someday amasses 65535 mithril, 65535 platinum, 99 silver, 99 copper for real, and then picks up 1 copper and has his money set to zero. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usepnir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sepnir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/23/01 6:54:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://sepnir.homestead.com/files/image3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .....</span><hr size=1> Well the problem is, that 65,000 platinum should be turning into 65 mithril, so something is bugged there. What did you loot the chest off? Something in a dungeon that wasn't quite finished perhaps? Just let mythic know. <p><img src=http://www.sepnir.homestead.com/files/sig.jpg ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubobbinsrumblebelly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobbins Rumblebelly</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://rcloues.home.mindspring.com/images/smiley.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/23/01 9:35:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://rcloues.home.mindspring.com/images/ezboard_icon.jpg width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Is this an exploit....?</span><hr size=1> My guess is that the number of coins per category is capped at 65535... (the highest value of a 4-byte signed int).  So, when you've got 65535 mithril and 65535 gold, it can't convert any more gold to mithril so it just leaves it alone.<br>
<br>
That's some pretty shoddy programming ;p<br>
